content.text:
The issue was caused by `ImportOrderingRule` incorrectly inserting blank lines before the first import when the `ij_kotlin_imports_layout` configuration contained `|` (blank line) separators that appeared before the group matching the first import.

For example, with `ij_kotlin_imports_layout = *, |, javax.**, java.**` and imports starting with `java.util.List`:
1. The `java.util.List` import matches `java.**`.
2. The code iterates from the "start" (index -1) to the index of `java.**`.
3. It finds `|` in between and inserts a blank line.
4. Since this is the first import, the blank line is inserted at the beginning of the import list, causing unwanted vertical spacing (e.g., double blank lines if there was already one after the package declaration).

The fix involves checking if we are processing the very first import (where `prev` is `null`) and skipping the blank line insertion check in that case. This ensures that blank lines defined in the layout are only inserted *between* imports, not before the first one.

I modified `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/ImportOrderingRule.kt` to implement this check.

Verified the fix with a reproduction test case and ensured existing tests pass.

```kotlin
// ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/ImportOrderingRule.kt

// ... inside sortedImports.fold loop ...

                    var hasBlankLines = false
                    // FIX: Only check for blank lines if there is a previous import (prev != null).
                    // This prevents inserting blank lines before the first import.
                    if (prev != null) {
                        for (i in (index1 + 1) until index2) {
                            if (importSorter.patterns[i] == PatternEntry.BLANK_LINE_ENTRY) {
                                hasBlankLines = true
                                break
                            }
                        }
                    }
                    if (hasBlankLines) {
                        sortedImportsWithSpaces += PsiWhiteSpaceImpl("\n\n")
                    }
                    sortedImportsWithSpaces += current
// ...
```

